# Vercel env automation

The Vercel Cursor plugin is **read-only** for environment variables. To set or update them, use the project script:

```bash
bash scripts/sync-vercel-env.sh
```

## Prerequisites (one-time, human)

1. Copy `.env.vercel-sync.example` → `.env.vercel-sync` (gitignored) **or** `~/.config/crm/deploy.env`
2. Fill in:
   - `VERCEL_TOKEN` from https://vercel.com/account/tokens
   - `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` from Supabase Dashboard → API Keys
   - `POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL` and `POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING` from Supabase → Database

After that, agents can run the sync script in any session — no dashboard, no GitHub CLI, no Vercel CLI.

Do **not** commit `.env.vercel-sync` or paste secrets into chat.
